title: Moonwalk
subTitle: Inspired and captivated by Michael Jackson, a group of small-town boys strive to master breakdancing and mimic his iconic moves.

title: Athisayan
subTitle: Devan, an orphan, drinks an invisibility potion and sets out to rescue Maya, a journalist who is raising him, after she is kidnapped by an influential man.

title: Mizhi Thurakku
subTitle: Savithri's family is attacked, after which she seeks refuge in a man's house. However, she soon experiences the evils of casteism.

title: Four Friends
subTitle: Roy, Amir, Soorya and Gauri are four cancer patients seeking treatment at the same hospital. They become friends and decide to help each other fulfil their dreams.

title: Kerala Varma Pazhassiraja
subTitle: In 1796, Kerala Varma, king of Pazhassi, leaves his kingdom due to the East India Company and seeks refuge in the Wayanad forests. He then uses guerrilla warfare tactics against his enemies.

title: China Town
subTitle: Mathukutty, Zachariah and Binoy, whose fathers were friends twenty years ago, return to Goa in order to reclaim a casino. But they face many challenges when a local goon tries to plot against them.

title: Kantara
subTitle: When greed paves the way for betrayal, scheming and murder, a young tribal reluctantly dons the traditions of his ancestors to seek justice.

title: Marakkar Arabikkadalinte Simham
subTitle: The naval chieftain of the Zamorin of Calicut, Kunjali Marakkar IV, develops a highly-equipped naval defence to fight against the Portuguese invaders in India.

title: Two Countries
subTitle: Ullas schemes to marry Simran, woman with a disability, to avoid repaying a debt, but faces complications when Laya, a wealthy alcoholic, enters his life, turning his plans upside down.

title: Nerariyan CBI
subTitle: Years after a young woman, Mythili, is murdered in a supposedly haunted mansion, Sethurama Iyer, a CBI officer, decides to find the culprit and solve the mystery.

title: Nerariyan CBI
subTitle: Years after a young woman, Mythili, is murdered in a supposedly haunted mansion, Sethurama Iyer, a CBI officer, decides to find the culprit and solve the mystery.

title: Swarnam
subTitle: Divakaran is a selfish and miserly man. When he fails to buy a truck for himself, he goes after a mythical treasure hidden in a river.

title: Seelabathi
subTitle: Seelabhati along with her mother visits a remote village where she starts working as a computer teacher. When some students mysteriously disappear, the villagers start blaming her educational course.

title: The Metro
subTitle: An anthology of three stories. The first story involves a murder investigation, the second story is about a group of goons following a girl, the third involves five friends delivering a package.

title: Chirikkum Thalika
subTitle: A comprehensive compilation of some of the best rib-tickling comedy scenes from various Malayalam movies featuring renowned actors and actresses.

title: Sherlock Toms
subTitle: Inspired by Sherlock Holmes, an IRS officer, resolves to employ his analytical prowess in tackling an extensive criminal operation.

title: Kadha Parayumbol
subTitle: Balan, a barber, struggles to give his family a better living. However, his life changes when his old friend, who is a film star, comes to his village for a film shoot.

title: Karyasthan
subTitle: After a past incident, two powerful clans of Krishnapuram remain estranged until one day, a man with a mysterious past decides to bring the families together.

title: Malikappuram
subTitle: A young aspiring film director who seeks to make his directorial debut decides to use a real-life gangster as inspiration for his first movie.

title: Pushpa 2: The Rule
subTitle: A powerful smuggler goes head-to-head with a vengeful enemy while controlling politics and managing high-stakes confrontations. A public apology sparks a tense showdown, culminating in a challenge.

title: Kuttanpillayude Sivarathri
subTitle: When Kuttan Pillai dies during Shivarathri, he returns as a ghost, observing his family's struggles and their conflicts over a cherished tree.

title: Kuttanpillayude Sivarathri
subTitle: When Kuttan Pillai dies during Shivarathri, he returns as a ghost, observing his family's struggles and their conflicts over a cherished tree.

title: Veera Simha Reddy
subTitle: Jai Simha Reddy, the son of the esteemed Veera Simha Reddy, returns home to avenge his father's death as a result of village politics.

title: Bhramam
subTitle: Ray, a pianist, pretends to be a visually impaired man. However, things take a turn for the worse when he unwittingly gets involved in the murder of a former actor.

title: Teja Bhai and Family
subTitle: Teja Bhai, a gangster falls in love with Vedhika, a simple girl. He has to leave his criminal life behind in order to seek her father's consent to marry her.

title: Vinodayathra
subTitle: Vinod, a quarrelsome young man, moves into his sister's house in a village to get his life in order. There, he happens to meet Anupama and falls in love with her.

title: Drishyam 2
subTitle: Georgekutty, a cinema hall owner, is a changed man who thrives in life. However, when his family become entangled in a criminal investigation, he must protect them from the legal institution.

title: Thrissur Pooram
subTitle: Pullu Giri is trying to live a peaceful life and forget his ruffian past. Following an incident, he gets dragged into the affairs of some local gangs.

title: Christian Brothers
subTitle: When the daughter of a minister gets kidnapped, Christy is called upon to rescue her. Although he manages to save her, he himself gets embroiled in the kidnapper's murder.

title: Nadodimannan
subTitle: Padmanabhan, a man who joins political rallies to make money, gets into trouble when he is elected mayor of Thiruvananthapuram and is forced to fight corruption in the city.
